Dayo Ojerinde The Chairman, Medical Advisory Committee of the Lagos University Teaching Hospital, Idi-Araba, Prof. Wasiu Adeyemo, has said the index Lassa fever patient will be discharged soon. In an interview with our correspondent on Monday, Adeyemo said the patient’s condition was improving and would soon be discharged. “The patient’s condition is improving and we are hoping to discharge him soon. The family members come to see him all the time. The commissioner was here last week and he is doing very well,” he said. Recall that the Lagos State on February 19 recorded a case of the Lassa hemorrhagic fever who was isolated at LUTH isolation centre. According to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, 118 people have died from Lassa fever in Nigeria since the onset of the outbreak in January. The NCDC, is its week eight report, revealed that the number of new confirmed cases had decreased from 115 in week seven to 102 cases in week eight. “Cumulatively, from week one to week 8, 2020, 118 deaths have been reported, with a Case Fatality Rate of 17.1 per cent which is lower than the CFR for the same period in 2019 (21.8 per cent). “In total, for 2020, 27 states have recorded at least one confirmed case across 115 local government areas,” the NCDC said in the report. Copyright PUNCH.
